This directory contains methods for taking steps.

Every method is assumed to take *at least* the following required arguments:
    0) vc,    the ambient vector configuration
    1) t,     the K\"ahler parameters
    2) step,  the step one wants to take (t->t+step)
There are also the assumed optional requirements
    3) triang, the triangulation defined by t
    3) kappa,  the intersection numbers of triang
        -) if not provided, then no intersection number computations will be
           performed
    4) verbosity, an integer indicating the level of diagnostics to print

Every method is assumed to output *exactly* the following:
    0) success, whether the step succeeded
    1) t+step,  the K\"ahler parameters after the step
    2) triang,  the triangulation defined by t+step (i.e.,
       `vc.subdivide(heights=vc.jorp(t+step))`)
    3) kappa,   the intersection numbers
    4) anc,     miscellaneous anciliary data

In general, any progress towards the update t->t+step will be accepted, even if
this means taking a shorter step (e.g., t->t+0.7*step)
